content:
To make the background cover the entire page without any margins or paddings, you can add the following CSS to the body element:
```css
body {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  background-color: #e8e8e8;
  font-family: 'DM Sans',sans-serif;
  text-align: center;
  /* Add these lines */
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  bottom: 0;
}
```
This will set the position of the body to be absolute and fill the entire viewport, effectively removing any margins or paddings. The `top`, `left`, `right`, and `bottom` properties set the position of the body to be at the edges of the viewport. The `position` property needs to be set to `absolute` to allow the `top`, `left`, `right`, and `bottom` properties to work.
